WEBVTT

00:04.104 --> 00:06.740
[GERMAN ACCENT] AH, THERE.

00:06.740 --> 00:09.709
IT COVERS 2/3
OF THE EARTH'S SURFACE.

00:09.709 --> 00:14.614
2/3 OF THE WORLD'S
MAGICAL CREATURES
IN ITS DEPTHS?

00:14.614 --> 00:17.684
WE CAN DRAW
BUT ONE CONCLUSION--

00:17.684 --> 00:18.752
I HAVE
A BEEF JERKY HEAD.

00:18.752 --> 00:22.255
NOW WATCH ME DANCE
THE CHA-CHA.

00:22.255 --> 00:25.925
THAT ROTWOOD PUPPY
IS FOR SERIOUS
MESSED UP, SPUDS.

00:25.925 --> 00:29.529
YEAH, YO, BUT YOU GOT
THE VOICE ALL WRONG.
CHECK THIS.

00:29.529 --> 00:31.998
[IMITATES ROTWOOD] YOU KIDS
WANT TO SEE MAGICAL CREATURES?

00:31.998 --> 00:37.070
CHECK OUT ALL ZE NASTY
NOSE TROLLS AND GAS MONSTER
I GOT IN MY--

00:37.070 --> 00:40.040
I WAS QUITE
THE POOPENSPIELER
BACK IN MY DAY, TOO,

00:40.040 --> 00:42.609
MR. MARIONETTE
MOCKERY MAN.
HEY!

00:42.609 --> 00:44.911
SHALL WE SEE
IF I'VE STILL GOT IT?

00:44.911 --> 00:50.784
I AM BEEF JERKY JAKE LONG,
AND I'M A REAL JERK-Y!

00:50.784 --> 00:53.019
HA HA HA HA.
I'M SORRY, BRAH,

00:53.019 --> 00:56.756
BUT YOU GOTTA ADMIT,
THAT WAS SOME SWEET
POOPENSPIELING.

00:56.756 --> 00:59.025
PRINCIPAL'S OFFICE, NOW!

00:59.025 --> 01:01.828
THIS IS YOUR 37TH TRIP
TO MY OFFICE

01:01.828 --> 01:03.730
IN THE YEAR
I'VE BEEN HERE, JAKE.

01:03.730 --> 01:10.136
YOUR GRADES ARE SLIPPING,
THERE'S BEEN A HUG UPTICK
IN ABSENCES AND TARDYS.

01:10.136 --> 01:13.807
I'VE READ
YOUR PERMANENT RECORD.
YOU WEREN'T ALWAYS LIKE THIS.

01:13.807 --> 01:16.676
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU
THIS PAST YEAR?

01:16.676 --> 01:21.781
IT'S, UH, BEEN, YOU KNOW,
LOTS OF...

01:21.781 --> 01:24.851
WELL, IT'S HIGH TIME
YOU CHANGED BACK.

01:24.851 --> 01:29.689
AND I'M AFRAID I'M GOING TO
HAVE TO TALK TO YOUR PARENTS
ABOUT HOW TO DO JUST THAT.

01:29.689 --> 01:32.625
MY PARENTS? YOU CAN'T.
I...

01:32.625 --> 01:34.627
WHAT THE...? FU?

01:34.627 --> 01:35.795
EXCUSE ME?

01:35.795 --> 01:39.632
I WAS JUST SAYING,
PHEW, WHAT THE...

01:39.632 --> 01:42.035
HECK TOOK US SO LONG
TO HAVE THIS TALK?

01:42.035 --> 01:46.106
NO, YOU SAID FU.
THERE WAS CLEARLY NO "YA" SOUND
IN THE MIDDLE.

01:46.106 --> 01:48.675
UH, I THINK THERE'S A PROBLEM,
AND I NEED TO--

01:48.675 --> 01:50.977
WE'RE NOT DONE HERE,
MR. LONG.

01:50.977 --> 01:54.747
YEAH,
I'M SURE THEY'D LOVE TO CHAT,
BUT MY PARENTS ARE OUT OF TOWN

01:54.747 --> 01:57.684
AT SOME JUNIOR
GENIUS CONVENTION
FOR MY LITTLE SISTER.

01:57.684 --> 02:00.753
IT'S JUST ME AND GRAMPS
KICKING IT AT THE CRIB AND--

02:00.753 --> 02:04.791
AW, MAN. I REALLY GOTTA GO.

02:04.791 --> 02:07.961
ACH, NOW THAT'S
JUST WRONG.

02:07.961 --> 02:12.298
YES, JAKE, SOMETHING HERE
IS VERY WRONG.

02:12.298 --> 02:16.369
AND IT'S ABOUT TIME
I FOUND OUT WHAT IT IS.

02:16.369 --> 02:19.772
♪ HE'S COOL, HE'S HOT
LIKE A FROZEN SUN ♪

02:19.772 --> 02:22.942
♪ HE'S YOUNG AND FAST,
HE'S THE CHOSEN ONE ♪

02:22.942 --> 02:26.146
♪ PEOPLE,
WE'RE NOT BRAGGIN' ♪

02:26.146 --> 02:29.883
♪ HE'S THE AMERICAN DRAGON ♪

02:29.883 --> 02:33.419
♪ HE'S GONNA STOP HIS ENEMIES
WITH HIS DRAGON POWER ♪

02:33.419 --> 02:37.290
♪ DRAGON TEETH, DRAGON TAIL,
BURNIN' DRAGON FIRE ♪

02:37.290 --> 02:38.958
♪ A REAL LIVE WIRE ♪

02:38.958 --> 02:41.961
♪ AMERICAN DRAGON ♪

02:42.662 --> 02:44.964
♪ AMERICAN DRAGON ♪

02:48.434 --> 02:51.838
♪ HE'S THE AMERICAN DRAGON ♪

02:51.838 --> 02:53.840
♪ HIS SKILLS ARE
GETTIN' FASTER ♪

02:53.840 --> 02:55.375
♪ WITH GRANDPA,
THE MASTER ♪

02:55.375 --> 02:57.110
♪ HIS DESTINY,
WHAT'S UP, G? ♪

02:57.110 --> 02:59.245
♪ IT'S SHOWTIME, BABY,
FOR THE LEGACY ♪

02:59.245 --> 03:02.815
♪ I'M A DRAGON,
AND I'M BRAGGIN' ♪

03:02.815 --> 03:06.953
♪ I'M THE MAGICAL PROTECTOR
FROM THE N.Y.C. ♪

03:06.953 --> 03:09.088
♪ YA HEARD? ♪

03:09.088 --> 03:11.824
♪ AMERICAN DRAGON ♪

03:11.824 --> 03:15.195
YEOW!

03:15.195 --> 03:19.065
YOU CAN'T JUST PULL ME
OUT OF DURSETTO'S OFFICE
LIKE THAT, GRAMPS.

03:19.065 --> 03:22.702
I GET ENOUGH HASSLE FROM YOU.
I DON'T NEED ANY MORE
FROM SCHOOL.

03:22.702 --> 03:26.172
I AM SORRY, JAKE,
BUT SOMETIMES
THE NEEDS OF OTHERS

03:26.172 --> 03:27.840
MUST COME
BEFORE YOUR OWN.

03:27.840 --> 03:30.009
I HAVE RECEIVED
A MOST DISTRESSING
MESSAGE

03:30.009 --> 03:32.178
FROM THE EAST RIVER
MERMAID CITY.

03:32.178 --> 03:33.980
THERE'S A MERMAID CITY?

03:33.980 --> 03:37.483
COULD THE BEDTIME STORIES
MY BELOVED NANA USED TO TELL ME
BE TRUE?

03:37.483 --> 03:40.486
COULD THERE REALLY BE
SUCH A MAGICAL PLACE?

03:40.486 --> 03:46.292
SO NOW WHAT? WE GOTTA
GO DIVING IN NEW YORK'S
FUNKIEST SWIMMING HOLE?

03:46.292 --> 03:49.295
OUR TRANSPORT
TO THE MERMAID CITY
WILL ARRIVE SHORTLY.

03:49.295 --> 03:51.731
THEY'RE PROBABLY STUCK
IN SQUIDLOCK.

03:51.731 --> 03:54.934
GAA GOO FLOOGY GOOGY.

03:54.934 --> 03:58.471
NOBODY GETS ME.

04:01.107 --> 04:02.208
FOLLOW ME.

04:02.208 --> 04:04.811
OH, NANA, DREAMS
DO COME TRUE!

04:04.811 --> 04:08.748
WHAT? YOU AND YOUR GRAMPS
NEVER HAD DREAMS?

04:08.748 --> 04:10.617
WHOA.

04:14.821 --> 04:19.759
[LAUGHTER] IT'S AS BEAUTIFUL
AS I ALWAYS DREAMED IT WOULD BE.

04:19.759 --> 04:26.065
LOOK AT THAT AND THAT
AND THAT AND THAT AND THAT.

04:26.065 --> 04:27.367
YO, SILVER?

04:27.367 --> 04:29.502
JAKE, I'M DELIGHTED
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

04:29.502 --> 04:32.205
HOW'S IT GOIN'
WITH THE WHOLE
FEAR-OF-WATER THING?

04:32.205 --> 04:34.374
NNN, YEAH, NOT SO GOOD.

04:34.374 --> 04:37.910
I HAD A BIT OF A RELAPSE
LAST CINCO DE MAYO.

04:37.910 --> 04:39.245
[MARIACHI MUSIC]

04:39.245 --> 04:42.148
TOP OFF YOUR AGUA,
SEÑORITA?

04:42.148 --> 04:46.419
BUT I'VE GOT A GOOD JOB IN
MERMAID DRYLANDER RELATIONS NOW.

04:46.419 --> 04:50.790
THAT'S WHY THEY SENT ME
TO TELL YOU ABOUT
OUR KELPY PROBLEM.

04:50.790 --> 04:52.825
AW, KELPY.
THAT SOUNDS CUTE.

04:52.825 --> 04:55.295
WELL, YOU CAN SET IT
TO CHILL, SIL,

04:55.295 --> 04:59.499
'CAUSE YOUR KELPY PROBLEM
IS MY NO PROBLEM.

04:59.499 --> 05:03.236
THIS IS SECURITY FOOTAGE
OF THE KELPY'S ESCAPE

05:03.236 --> 05:05.438
FROM OUR PRISON A YEAR AGO.

05:05.438 --> 05:09.042
NOT MUCH OF A KARAOKE VOICE
ON THAT ONE.

05:09.042 --> 05:12.879
IT'S A SHAPE-SHIFTER
OF THE ORDER VAMPIRA MORPHUS,

05:12.879 --> 05:15.248
ABLE TO ABSORB
THE FORM AND POWER

05:15.248 --> 05:19.986
OF ANY MAGICAL CREATURE
ON WHICH IT FEEDS.

05:21.054 --> 05:24.023
MANY OF OUR
BEST MERMAID DETECTIVES
HAVE SPENT THE PAST YEAR

05:24.023 --> 05:29.529
I FEEL YOU, SILVER.
NOT EVERYBODY CAN HACK IT
LIKE I MACK IT.

05:29.529 --> 05:30.997
THE AM DRAG IS HERE
FOR YOU.

05:30.997 --> 05:33.232
ACTUALLY, WE CALLED YOU
DOWN HERE TO WARN YOU.

05:33.232 --> 05:36.202
THERE'S BEEN A FLURRY
OF KELPY ATTACKS AROUND
YOUR NEIGHBORHOOD RECENTLY.

05:36.202 --> 05:38.905
WE THINK IT MAY HAVE FOUND OUT
WHAT YOU ARE,

05:38.905 --> 05:41.441
AND IT'S LOOKING TO FEED
ON YOUR DRAGON POWER.

05:41.441 --> 05:42.975
WHOA, REWIND AND REMIX.

05:42.975 --> 05:49.849
HE WON'T ACTUALLY EAT YOU.
HE'LL SLOWLY DRAIN YOUR ESSENCE
WITH HIS ICY-COLD BITE,

05:49.849 --> 05:51.517
SENDING YOUR SOUL
INTO ETERNAL DARKNESS

05:51.517 --> 05:53.953
AND LEAVING YOUR LIFELESS HUSK
OF A BODY BEHIND.

05:53.953 --> 05:55.521
OH, THAT'S NOT
MUCH BETTER, IS IT?

05:55.521 --> 05:58.925
WELL, I GUESS IT'S NICE
THAT YOU GET TO KEEP YOUR HUSK.

05:58.925 --> 06:00.927
SPUD? WHERE'D THAT BOY GO?

06:00.927 --> 06:05.431
UH, I DON'T MEAN TO BAG ON
YOUR CONSTRUCTION,

06:05.431 --> 06:09.001
BUT THERE'S NOT MUCH GIVE
IN THESE BUBBLES.

06:09.001 --> 06:13.206
SO BEAUTIFUL. OHH.

06:13.206 --> 06:15.375
AND DID YOU KNOW
THAT IN MERMOPOLIS,

06:15.375 --> 06:19.312
YOU CAN FALL ASLEEP
EVERY NIGHT TO THE SONGS
OF PASSING DOLPHINS?

06:19.312 --> 06:20.913
LOOK, I FOUND AN MP3.

06:20.913 --> 06:24.317
[DOLPHINS VOCALIZING]

06:24.317 --> 06:28.454
IT'S LIKE MUSIC THAT
ONLY MY HEART UNDERSTANDS.

06:28.454 --> 06:30.957
[IMITATES DOLPHINS]

06:30.957 --> 06:33.126
[SPEAKS CHINESE]

06:33.126 --> 06:36.963
WHY AM I HEARING DOLPHIN SONGS?
IT IS KELPY WE ARE AFTER!

06:36.963 --> 06:38.431
WE'RE ON IT, GRAMPS.

06:38.431 --> 06:40.299
FOR REAL,
I'M GETTIN' PUNKED HERE.

06:40.299 --> 06:43.569
MY FOLKS ARE OUTTA TOWN.
WE SHOULD BE OUT
ALL NIGHT PARTYING,

06:43.569 --> 06:45.972
PLAYING VIDEO GAMES,
YOU KNOW, WHATEVER.

06:45.972 --> 06:48.207
WHY DOES HE ALWAYS GOTTA
COME ON SO HARDCORE?

06:48.207 --> 06:54.046
I HEARD THAT. THEN
HE'D HAVE NO TIME TO BE
STEALIN' AWAY MY TIME.

06:54.046 --> 06:56.182
TOO BAD THERE'S NOTHING
WE CAN DO.
HOO HOO HOO.

06:56.182 --> 07:00.219
SORRY, LADIES, THERE'S ONLY
SO MUCH OF THE FU TO GO AROUND.

07:00.219 --> 07:04.490
CHECK IT OUT. THE WORLD'S ONLY
ONLINE MAGICAL DATING SERVICE?

07:04.490 --> 07:08.628
I GOTTA TELL YA, IT'S
WAY EASIER THAN DATING WAS
IN THE OLD DAYS.

07:08.628 --> 07:10.663
[FANFARE PLAYS]

07:10.663 --> 07:12.398
HUZZAH, FINE LASS.

07:12.398 --> 07:15.134
MY NAME IS FU DOG,
AND I--

07:15.134 --> 07:17.403
[WHINNIES]

07:21.307 --> 07:22.642
[WHIMPERS]

07:22.642 --> 07:24.143
YOU KNOW WHAT? KEEP HER.

07:24.143 --> 07:27.046
YOU PUT IN A LITTLE SOMETHING
ABOUT YOURSELF.

07:27.046 --> 07:30.583
"PUREBRED
AIREDALE TERRIER
WITH VACATION HOMES

07:30.583 --> 07:36.155
LOOK AT ALL THOSE TYPOS
IN MY BIO. YOU SHOULD
TRY TYPING WITH PAWS.

07:36.155 --> 07:39.358
ANYWAY, THEN YOU TELL 'EM
WHAT KIND OF DAME
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR,

07:39.358 --> 07:42.962
AND PALOOKAZOOM--
INSTANT LOVEY-DOVEY.

07:42.962 --> 07:46.199
SO, IF I WAS TO SAY
I WAS, FOR EXAMPLE,

07:46.199 --> 07:50.136
A MANLY HUNK
OF CHINESE DRAGON LOOKING
FOR A LITTLE SPICY CHOW MEIN

07:50.136 --> 07:51.671
TO NOODLE AROUND WITH...

07:51.671 --> 07:57.009
I DON'T KNOW IF GRAMPS
WANTS TO GET BACK INTO
THE SWINGING SINGLES' SCENE.

07:57.009 --> 07:59.312
HEY, I'M JUST DOING
WHAT HE TOLD ME--

07:59.312 --> 08:03.316
TAKING CARE
OF OTHER PEOPLE'S NEEDS.

08:03.649 --> 08:09.755
YOU KNOW I'D LOVE TO,
GRAMPS, BUT I GOTTA
STUDY UP ON THAT KELPY.

08:09.755 --> 08:12.358
[MUTTERS IN CHINESE]
YES?

08:12.358 --> 08:15.661
WELL, YOU GONNA
GIVE ME SOME FLOWERS?

08:15.661 --> 08:19.065
I GOTTA SHOW UP
ON YOUR DOORSTEP FOR A DATE,

08:19.065 --> 08:22.168
I EXPECT AT LEAST
SOME POSIES FOR MY TROUBLES.

08:22.168 --> 08:25.571
DATE?
EH, FORGET IT.

08:26.138 --> 08:30.243
BLECCH. I CAN SEE
YOU GOT NO CLASS.

08:30.243 --> 08:34.013
THAT WAS CERTAINLY STRANGE.
[DOORBELL RINGS]

08:34.013 --> 08:39.217
HI THERE. I LIKE LONG WALKS
IN THE FULL MOONLIGHT--

08:40.753 --> 08:44.490
HI. SO MEET
TO GREAT YOU.
OH, I MEAN--

08:44.490 --> 08:47.293
GREAT, SANDY.
YOU RUINED IT AGAIN!

08:47.293 --> 08:50.129
YES, I KNOW
I'M A SHARKWOMAN,

08:50.129 --> 08:51.531
BUT I LOVE
AND I FEEL,

08:51.531 --> 08:55.701
AND I'D REALLY LIKE TO
TRY TO MAKE THIS WORK.

08:56.502 --> 09:02.508
I'M TRYING TO HELP A LONELY,
CRANKY, NO-GIRLFRIEND-HAVIN'
BROTHER OUT.

09:02.508 --> 09:04.777
[EERIE SCREECHING]
WHAT THE...?

09:04.777 --> 09:07.547
DRAGON UP!

09:10.783 --> 09:13.553
EASY, LITTLE GUY.
WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

09:13.553 --> 09:16.355
IT ATTACKED US OUT OF NOWHERE.
PLEASE SAVE US.

09:16.355 --> 09:18.057
FROM WHAT?
WHAT'S OUT THERE?

09:18.057 --> 09:21.427
K-K-K-K-K-KELPY!

09:23.329 --> 09:27.133
HAAH! YO, KELPY, YOU WANNA
THROW DOWN THE HARSH,

09:27.133 --> 09:30.436
BRING IT TO
THE AM DRAG, CHUMP.

09:30.670 --> 09:32.705
[GROWLS]

09:32.705 --> 09:35.641
SO THAT'S HOW WE PLAY IT, HUH?
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

09:35.641 --> 09:39.545
WHEN YOU WANNA BRING IT,
I'LL BE WAITING.

09:40.546 --> 09:42.848
SOON, YES, VERY SOON,

09:42.848 --> 09:49.422
I BUILD MY POWER AND FIND A WAY
TO STRIKE FROM THE INSIDE.

09:51.290 --> 09:52.592
[LAUGHTER]

09:52.592 --> 09:55.661
WHAT THE...? GRAMPS AND...

09:55.661 --> 09:57.663
HE FOUND HIMSELF A LADY.

09:57.663 --> 10:01.367
HEY, GRAMPS,
WHO'S THE LUCKY--
PRINCIPAL DURSETTO?

10:01.367 --> 10:03.669
AH, JAKE, WE THOUGHT
YOU HAD FALLEN ASLEEP.

10:03.669 --> 10:07.640
HOW DID THE WEBSITE
AND YOU AND HER--HUH?

10:07.640 --> 10:09.875
I CAME HERE TO TALK
WITH YOUR PARENTS.

10:09.875 --> 10:11.677
I KNOW YOU SAID
THEY WERE OUT OF TOWN,

10:11.677 --> 10:16.182
BUT, TO BE HONEST, I FIGURED
YOU WERE LYING. SORRY.

10:16.182 --> 10:17.617
NO NEED TO APOLOGIZE.

10:17.617 --> 10:20.486
JAKE OFTEN HAS PROBLEMS
WITH DISHONESTY,

10:20.486 --> 10:22.655
NOT TO MENTION
DISCIPLINE, FOCUS...

10:22.655 --> 10:24.557
Both: STUDY HABITS. OH.

10:24.557 --> 10:29.595
PERHAPS YOU WOULD LIKE
TO DISCUSS JAKE'S ISSUES
WITH ME INSTEAD.

10:29.595 --> 10:31.831
SAY OVER DINNER?
OH...

10:31.831 --> 10:33.766
IT'S A DATE.

10:33.766 --> 10:34.867
NO-O-O-O-O!

10:37.903 --> 10:46.479
JAKE, DOES YOUR GRANDFATHER
PREFER EASY LISTENING
OR SMOOTH JAZZ?

10:46.479 --> 10:51.317
JAKE, GO RENT US
A ROMANTIC MOVIE WHILE WE
DISCUSS YOUR MANY PROBLEMS.

10:51.317 --> 10:56.355
JAKE, I BELIEVE YOUR GRANDFATHER
SENT SOMETHING WITH YOU.

10:56.355 --> 10:59.258
AH, YES, MA'AM.

10:59.258 --> 11:04.363
"TILL NEXT WE MEET,
A ROSE TO REMIND YOU--OH--

11:04.363 --> 11:06.532
YOU ARE MY SWEET."

11:06.532 --> 11:08.200
[LAUGHTER]

11:08.200 --> 11:10.903
AREN'T WE SWEET.

11:12.371 --> 11:16.208
A'IGHT, SO IT DIDN'T WORK OUT
EXACTLY LIKE WE THOUGHT.

11:16.208 --> 11:17.576
YOU MIND KEEPING IT DOWN?

11:17.576 --> 11:21.280
I FOUND ME A CUTE FRENCH POODLE
NAMED LA BETTY 42,

11:21.280 --> 11:22.415
AND, OOH, LA LA,

11:22.415 --> 11:26.652
ANY WOMAN WHO MAKE ME LOL
ON MY PC 24/7

11:26.652 --> 11:28.754
IS A-OK WITH M-E.

11:28.754 --> 11:31.791
[EERIE SCREECHING]

11:33.259 --> 11:36.495
LET ME CHECK IT OUT.

11:36.896 --> 11:40.633
HELLO? SOMEBODY OUT HERE?

11:40.633 --> 11:42.702
WHOA.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.603
WHOA, GIRL.

11:44.603 --> 11:49.508
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU?
KELPY BITE.

11:49.508 --> 11:50.810
COME ON NOW. YOU'RE OK.

11:50.810 --> 11:52.978
LOOKS LIKE YOU GOT AWAY
BEFORE HE FINISHED FEEDING.

11:52.978 --> 11:55.881
LET'S JUST GET YOU
SOMEWHERE SAFE AND--

11:55.881 --> 11:58.517
[KELPY SCREECHES]

11:59.885 --> 12:01.854
PRINCIPAL DURSETTO?
OH.

12:01.854 --> 12:06.425
JAKE. I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE--
I DIDN'T MEAN TO SCARE YOU.

12:06.425 --> 12:08.594
I THINK MY CHAIR
RUSTED UP A LITTLE.

12:08.594 --> 12:10.596
WHAT ARE YOU DOING BACK HERE?

12:10.596 --> 12:13.699
WE JUST GOT BACK.
I CAME TO SAY GOOD NIGHT.

12:13.699 --> 12:15.501
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING BACK HERE?

12:15.501 --> 12:20.372
I--I WAS JUST... IS THAT
SEAWEED ON YOUR CHAIR?

12:20.372 --> 12:24.009
OH, YES. WE, UH,
WENT TO THE BEACH.

12:24.009 --> 12:27.446
I AM STILL WAITING
FOR MY GOOD-NIGHT HUG.

12:27.446 --> 12:29.882
OR ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN A LIP-LOCK UPGRADE?

12:29.882 --> 12:32.918
Trix: HEY, YO, GRAMPS,
WE STILL STANDIN' HERE.

12:32.918 --> 12:35.688
I'LL SEE YOU
IN SCHOOL ON MONDAY.

12:35.688 --> 12:38.624
YEAH.

12:42.795 --> 12:43.996
DURSETTO?

12:43.996 --> 12:45.765
IT ALL FITS, TRIX.

12:45.765 --> 12:47.466
THE SCREECHING,
THE SEAWEED.

12:47.466 --> 12:53.572
HOW SHE'S ALWAYS
OVER AT MY PLACE, GETTING
ALL CLOSE TO GRAMPS AND ME.

12:53.572 --> 12:57.042
YEAH, GETTING CLOSE ENOUGH
TO SNEAK A BITE OF DRAGON

12:57.042 --> 12:58.677
THE SECOND
WE LET OUR GUARD DOWN.

12:58.677 --> 13:03.582
OK, MAYBE. BUT WHY ARE WE HERE
BUSTING INTO HER OFFICE

13:03.582 --> 13:05.451
AT DAG NASTY O'CLOCK
IN THE MORNING

13:05.451 --> 13:07.453
INSTEAD OF TELLING YOUR GRAMPS
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:07.453 --> 13:10.656
YOU THINK LOVER BOY GRAMPS
IS GONNA LISTEN TO
ANYTHING I SAY

13:10.656 --> 13:12.291
WITHOUT SOME KIND OF PROOF?

13:12.291 --> 13:15.327
A'IGHT, BUT I JUST GOT
ONE MORE QUESTION--

13:15.327 --> 13:17.930
WHO TOLD SPUD HE COULD
BRING THE FISH?

13:17.930 --> 13:20.366
WHY WON'T YOU TELL ME
YOUR SECRETS?

13:20.366 --> 13:23.602
IN MY HEART,
I'M ALREADY ONE OF YOU.

13:23.602 --> 13:26.839
GLUB GLUB. GLUB GLUB.
GLUB GLUB.

13:26.839 --> 13:29.675
GLUB GLUB...GLUB...GLUB.

13:29.675 --> 13:35.014
GLUB GLUB GLUB GLUB...
GLUB...GLUB.

13:35.614 --> 13:37.817
FISH TANKS, BLUE WALLS,
OCEAN MURALS.

13:37.817 --> 13:41.654
SHE'S DEFINITELY GOT
AN UNDERWATER THEME GOING ON.

13:41.654 --> 13:44.390
OOH, AND CHECK IT.
BROKEN CUFFS AND CHAINS.

13:44.390 --> 13:48.661
PRETTY RUSTED.
LOTS OF OLD SEA JUNK ON 'EM.

13:50.329 --> 13:52.731
EAST RIVER.
VINTAGE--LAST YEAR.

13:52.731 --> 13:56.635
LOOKS LIKE SOMEBODY WANTED TO
KEEP A SOUVENIR OF HER BREAKOUT.

13:56.635 --> 14:00.506
[CREAKING]
GO.

14:02.000 --> 14:08.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

14:09.882 --> 14:13.519
DON'T SAY MAYBE.
SAY YES TO GRANDPA.

14:13.519 --> 14:14.620
BABY.

14:14.620 --> 14:17.356
[SINGS IN CHINESE]

14:19.692 --> 14:22.127
CUT THE MIKE, G.
THIS IS SERIOUS.

14:22.127 --> 14:28.434
I'M SORRY. I KNOW WHAT
IT'S LIKE TO FIND OUT YOUR LADY
IS YOUR MORTAL ENEMY.

14:28.434 --> 14:30.102
BUT THIS PROVES IT.

14:30.102 --> 14:34.607
A RUSTED OLD CHAIN PROVES
ONLY THAT YOU ARE BOUND
TO YOUR OWN BIASES.

14:34.607 --> 14:37.743
I KNOW YOU MUST HAVE ISSUES
WITH MY DATING YOUR PRINCIPAL,

14:37.743 --> 14:39.144
BUT I THINK I WOULD KNOW

14:39.144 --> 14:41.513
IF THE ADMINISTRATOR OF MY HEART
WAS A KELPY.

14:41.513 --> 14:45.384
IF YOU DISCOVER ANY REAL LEADS
TO THE KELPY'S WHEREABOUTS,

14:45.384 --> 14:47.553
I SHALL BE BURNING
A MIX CD FOR TONIGHT.

14:47.553 --> 14:49.488
♪ I LOVE YOU,
YOU LOVE ME ♪

14:49.488 --> 14:52.124
♪ LET'S GO EAT
SOME SNOW PEAS... ♪

14:52.124 --> 14:53.726
MMM-MMM-MMM.

14:53.726 --> 14:56.028
THE THINGS
LOVE WILL DO TO A MAN.

14:56.028 --> 15:00.633
ALAS, LA BETTY 42, MY YACHT
IS IN THE SHOP RIGHT NOW.

15:00.633 --> 15:03.969
UH, NO, YOU CAN'T COME OVER
TO THE MANSION

15:03.969 --> 15:07.039
'CAUSE THERE WAS A TERRIBLE
CAVIAR SPILL IN THE POOL HOUSE,

15:07.039 --> 15:10.943
AND WE'RE RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF GOLD-PLATING THE BARS
ON THE MENAGERIE.

15:10.943 --> 15:12.478
[STAMMERS]

15:12.478 --> 15:14.413
LOOKS LIKE IT'S UP TO US.

15:14.413 --> 15:16.148
MM-HMM.
YEAH.

15:16.148 --> 15:19.551
UH, TO DO WHAT
EXACTLY?

15:19.551 --> 15:21.020
TO CATCH DURSETTO.

15:21.020 --> 15:24.123
[KNOCKING]

15:25.090 --> 15:27.726
PRINCY D, WHAT'S UP?

15:27.726 --> 15:33.465
YEAH, I JUST WANTED TO APOLOGIZE
FOR GIVING YOU AND MY GRAMPS
SUCH A HARD TIME,

15:33.465 --> 15:39.104
SO, YOU KNOW, IF YOU WANNA...
COME OUTSIDE AND TALK.

15:39.672 --> 15:44.910
IT'S A LITTLE COLD OUTSIDE.
WHY DON'T YOU COME IN HERE?

15:44.910 --> 15:47.579
ALL RIGHT, LET'S CUT
THE FRONTIN'.

15:47.579 --> 15:52.685
YEAH, I KNOW WHAT YOU ARE
AND WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO DO.

15:52.685 --> 15:56.221
ALL RIGHT, THIS DOESN'T
HAVE TO GET UGLY.

15:56.221 --> 15:59.725
LET'S JUST TALK
ABOUT IT LIKE--YAAH!

15:59.725 --> 16:03.929
WHOA. TRIX, SPUD!
DROP IT!

16:05.998 --> 16:11.136
DRAGON UP! NO MORE
RUNNING AWAY, KELPY!

16:13.505 --> 16:18.210
GOTCHA. AND THE CATCH OF THE DAY
IS FRESH UGLY KELPY.

16:18.210 --> 16:22.815
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
YOU'RE THE KELPY.

16:22.815 --> 16:27.653
YOU CAN'T RUN FOREVER.
I'M NOT THE ONLY MERMAID
WHO'S AFTER YOU.

16:27.653 --> 16:29.688
MERMAID?

16:31.190 --> 16:33.726
AW, MAN.

16:36.762 --> 16:39.698
I WAS ONE OF
THE MERMAID DETECTIVES

16:39.698 --> 16:44.837
I THOUGHT IT MIGHT BE YOU.
THE WAY I KEPT FINDING YOU
EVERYPLACE THE BEAST ATTACKED,

16:44.837 --> 16:48.607
THE CHANGES YOU SAID
YOU'D GONE THROUGH
IN THE PAST YEAR.

16:48.607 --> 16:52.578
I THOUGHT THE REAL JAKE LONG
HAD BEEN EATEN AND REPLACED.

16:52.578 --> 16:57.683
WHAT ABOUT THOSE CHAINS WE FOUND
WHEN WE BROKE INTO YOUR OFFICE?

16:57.683 --> 17:00.019
ACH, EVIDENCE
I PICKED UP ON THE--

17:00.019 --> 17:01.787
YOU BROKE INTO MY OFFICE?

17:01.787 --> 17:03.722
I THOUGHT YOU WERE TRYING
TO EAT ME AND GRAMPS.

17:03.722 --> 17:08.227
BUT IF YOU'RE NOT--
I MEAN, THAT MEANS
THE KELPY IS STILL...

17:08.227 --> 17:12.097
WHERE IS SHE? DOLORES PROMISED
SHE WOULD BE HERE BY NOW.

17:12.097 --> 17:15.034
HEY, I HEAR YA.
LIES CAN TOTALLY RUIN
THE RELATIONSHIP.

17:15.034 --> 17:18.037
TAKE IT FROM ME, A NOBEL
PEACE PRIZE-WINNING DOG

17:18.037 --> 17:20.873
WHO JUST WANTS THE PAPARAZZI
TO LEAVE HIM ALONE.

17:20.873 --> 17:23.142
AIN'T THAT RIGHT,
LA BETTY 42?

17:23.142 --> 17:25.144
GO FETCH ME A DRINK.

17:25.144 --> 17:27.246
RIGHT AWAY, BABY CAKES.

17:27.246 --> 17:28.714
I SHOULD CALL DOLORES.

17:28.714 --> 17:32.785
[SNARLS]
HMM? OH, IT'S YOU,
LA BETTY 42.

17:32.785 --> 17:36.755
THE REST ROOM
IS DOWN THE HALL.

17:36.755 --> 17:39.224
[KELPY MORPHS]

17:41.693 --> 17:45.998
DO YOU MIND, LA BETTY 42?
I AM TRYING TO--HYAH!

17:45.998 --> 17:48.133
[SCREECHES]

17:48.133 --> 17:52.838
I HOPE YOU LIKE
YOUR TAP WATER WARM,
BABY BECAUSE--AAH!

17:52.838 --> 17:56.575
WHEN I SAID YOU
COULD SLIP INTO SOMETHING
A LITTLE MORE COMFORTABLE,

17:56.575 --> 17:59.211
I DIDN'T MEAN TO--OOF.

17:59.211 --> 18:04.817
AND NOW THE FEASTING.

18:05.717 --> 18:09.154
AII. OHH...OHH.

18:09.154 --> 18:13.625
YO, MY GRAMPS
IS NOT SURF 'N' TURF.

18:13.625 --> 18:14.927
[SCREECHES]

18:14.927 --> 18:19.898
JAKE, NO. HE'S ABSORBED
YOUR GRANDFATHER'S POWER.

18:19.898 --> 18:22.167
[SCREAMS]

18:22.167 --> 18:26.638
I TOLD YOU I WOULD
FIND A WAY INSIDE, DRAGON.

18:26.638 --> 18:30.375
NOW YOUR POWER WILL BE MINE.

18:32.744 --> 18:35.147
AAH!

18:35.147 --> 18:36.748
YO, YO, COWBOY.

18:36.748 --> 18:40.719
CHECK THE AM DRAG
RIDING BAREBACK, BABY.

18:45.657 --> 18:48.227
JAKE, LOOK OUT.

18:48.227 --> 18:51.697
DON'T LET THE WHEELCHAIR
FOOL YOU.

18:51.697 --> 18:53.832
[SCREECHES]

18:55.067 --> 18:59.805
GOTCHA. HAH, WHO'S YOUR
MACK DADDY NOW, TINY?

19:01.874 --> 19:04.943
AW, MAN. WHEN DID HE
EAT A TROLL?

19:04.943 --> 19:09.414
BACK, SCUZ PASTE.
YOU MESS WITH ONE MERMAID,
YOU MESS WITH US ALL.

19:09.414 --> 19:12.151
SORRY WE LATE.
HOMIE OVER HERE
MADE US STOP

19:12.151 --> 19:13.719
TO GET HIS
MERMAID COSTUME.

19:13.719 --> 19:19.324
MERMAN, TRIXIE. YOU GOTTA
CHILL-ATE WITH THE GILL HATE.

19:19.324 --> 19:25.164
QUICK, HELP ME UP
SO I CAN SLAP THAT PUNK
WITH MY MIGHTY FIN.

19:25.164 --> 19:27.766
HIGHER, HIGHER.

19:33.005 --> 19:35.774
HUH? YAAH!

19:35.774 --> 19:39.678
WE ARE NEVER GOING TO BEAT HIM
IF HE KEEPS CHANGING FORM
LIKE THAT.

19:39.678 --> 19:44.716
THEN I GUESS I GOTTA
CONVINCE HIM TO STAY PUT
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

19:44.716 --> 19:46.718
CHECK IT, I GOT A PLAN.

19:46.718 --> 19:49.821
TASTE...MY...MERMAID...FURY.

19:49.821 --> 19:52.991
OH, HANDLE YOUR BUSINESS.
IT'S ALL YOU, PLAYA.

19:52.991 --> 19:56.061
YO, SCARED TO TAKE ME ON
AS YOURSELF, CHUMP?

19:56.061 --> 19:58.830
OR ARE YOU AS WEAK
AS YOU ARE UGLY?

19:58.830 --> 20:01.700
YES. A MEAL LIKE DRAGON

20:01.700 --> 20:04.903
DESERVES TO BE CONSUMED
WITH MY OWN TEETH.

20:04.903 --> 20:09.408
I FEED ON
YOUNG, STRONG DRAGON.

20:09.408 --> 20:11.944
DURSETTO, GO!

20:11.944 --> 20:13.879
AAH!

20:13.879 --> 20:15.847
UH, JUST SO YOU KNOW,
SWEETIE,

20:15.847 --> 20:20.085
I'M GONNA NEED
SOME EXTRA CREDIT FOR THIS.

20:21.954 --> 20:26.892
LA BETTY 42,
I'M DISGUSTED WITH YOU.

20:26.892 --> 20:28.961
HOW COULD YOU
SO MISREPRESENT YOURSELF?

20:28.961 --> 20:32.965
WHEN I WAS BACK IN THE
ROYAL NAVY BEFORE I MADE
MY FORTUNE IN RUBY MINING,

20:32.965 --> 20:34.900
WE HAD A NAME
FOR PEOPLE LIKE YOU!

20:34.900 --> 20:37.469
I'M SORRY
I MISJUDGED YOU,
JAKE.

20:37.469 --> 20:40.305
ME, TOO. AND I JUST
WANT YOU TO KNOW,

20:40.305 --> 20:43.809
IF YOU AND GRAMPS WANNA,
YOU KNOW, GET SERIOUS,

20:43.809 --> 20:45.244
I'M COOL WITH THAT.

20:45.244 --> 20:48.880
OH, I...I ASSUMED YOU KNEW.

20:48.880 --> 20:50.749
NOW THAT THE KELPY
HAS BEEN CAPTURED,

20:50.749 --> 20:53.785
DETECTIVE DURSETTO MUST TAKE
A NEW UNDERCOVER ASSIGNMENT.

20:53.785 --> 20:57.489
WHAT? BUT THAT'S NOT FAIR!
THEY CAN'T--

20:57.489 --> 21:03.895
BUT SOMETIMES THE NEEDS
OF OTHERS MUST COME BEFORE
OUR OWN, YOUNG DRAGON.

21:03.895 --> 21:06.298
AND SO, I GUESS THIS IS...

21:06.298 --> 21:09.835
TAKE ME WITH YOU,
PLEASE.

21:09.835 --> 21:10.769
GOODBYE.

21:10.769 --> 21:14.373
FAREWELL,
MY CHERRY BLOSSOM.

21:15.140 --> 21:19.444
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.
I'M REALLY GOING.

21:19.444 --> 21:21.813
WHEE!

21:21.813 --> 21:27.386
WAIT. DO OVER.
I BREATHED IN A MINNOW.

21:27.386 --> 21:31.490
I TOTALLY GOT AWAY WITH
NOT HAVING DURSETTO
TALK TO MY PARENTS.

21:31.490 --> 21:35.827
AND NOW THAT THERE'S
GONNA BE A NEW PRINCIPAL,
I GET A CLEAN SLATE.

21:35.827 --> 21:39.164
STUDENTS, I HAVE
ZE SAD DUTY TO INFORM YOU

21:39.164 --> 21:42.801
THAT DUE TO THE DISORDER
CAUSED BY MISS DURSETTO'S
SUDDEN DEPARTURE,

21:42.801 --> 21:47.339
I WILL NO LONGER BE ABLE
TO SERVE AS YOUR TEACHER.

21:47.339 --> 21:49.508
[CHEERING]

21:49.508 --> 21:51.843
INSTEAD I HAVE CHOSEN TO BE

21:51.843 --> 21:54.546
YOUR NEW PRINCIPAL. TA-DA!

21:54.546 --> 21:58.216
[ALL COMPLAIN]

21:58.216 --> 21:59.918
I HAD TO SPECIAL ORDER
THE BERET.

21:59.918 --> 22:02.587
NOT OFFICIAL PRINCIPAL WEAR,
BUT WHAT DO YOU THINK?

22:02.587 --> 22:03.655
CLASSY, NO?

22:03.655 --> 22:05.424
AW, MAN.

22:08.460 --> 22:14.466
THAT'S A FISH ON BOTTOM
AND ALL LADY ON TOP? DURSETTO!

22:14.466 --> 22:16.868
WHO CAN RUN A JUNIOR HIGH
ON THE SLY

22:16.868 --> 22:20.539
AND ALWAYS GETS HER GUY?
DURSETTO!

22:20.539 --> 22:23.475
UNDERCOVER, UNDERWATER.

22:23.475 --> 22:25.177
AW, YEAH.

22:25.177 --> 22:27.446
DURSETTO--MERMAID DETECTIVE.

22:27.446 --> 22:31.483
OOH, CALL UP
THE MAGIC CHANNEL, KID.

22:31.483 --> 22:36.388
FU SMELLS A NEW HIT SHOW.
GAA GOO FLOOGY GOOGY.

22:36.388 --> 22:37.389
NOBODY GETS ME.

